content:
Add and Remove Local Salesforce Objects and Fields from Data Sync

Update data sync to keep up with your changing business by adding local Salesforce objects, removing objects, and managing which fields are synced. Synced data is stored in CRM Analytics as objects that you can use in recipes.

From Data Manager, click the Connections tab. All objects configured to sync are listed under their connection name. The default local connection is SFDC_LOCAL.
To add an object and its fields:
Next to a local connection, click  and select Edit Objects.
Find the object to add by scrolling or using the search bar, and select it.
Select the fields that you want to sync.
Optionally, edit the fieldâ€™s attributes or filter the data synced to CRM Analytics from Data Sync Filter.
Click Save.

To add or remove a field from data sync for an object already configured for sync:
From the Connections tab, select the connection associated with the object. Use the search bar to find the connection and object if you have many connections. The connection's associated objects are listed.
Click the name of the object to see its columns. Fields already included for sync are selected.
To add a field, select the checkbox next to the field. To remove a field, deselect the checkbox next to the field.
Click Save.

To remove, or disconnect, an object from data sync:
From the Connections tab, select the connection associated with the object. Use the search bar to find the connection and object if you have many connections. The connection's associated objects are listed.
Click the menu  to the right of the object you want to remove.
Click Disconnect Object.
Click Disconnect.

NOTE Remove the object from all recipes before you disconnect. Data sync stops pulling data from the data source to CRM Analytics when you disconnect an object. This impacts recipes and other assets that use this synced data.
title: Manage Local Salesforce Data Sync in CRM Analytics
